    {
      "title": "Quadriliteral Verb Forms",
      "titleArabic": "أوزان الفعل الرباعي",
      "content": [
        "Quadriliteral verbs have four root letters. Besides the basic form فَعْلَلَ, there are three augmented (mazīd) patterns that add meaning modifications."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Basic: فَعْلَلَ - تَرْجَمَ (to translate)",
        "Augmented 1: تَفَعْلَلَ (reflexive) - تَدَحْرَجَ (to roll)",
        "Augmented 2: اِفْعَنْلَلَ - اِطْمَأَنَّ (to be at peace)",
        "Augmented 3: اِفْعَلَلَّ - اِقْشَعَرَّ (to shiver)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "تَرْجَمَ الْكِتَابَ", "english": "He translated the book" },
        { "arabic": "تَدَحْرَجَتِ الْكُرَةُ", "english": "The ball rolled" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Adverb of Time and Place (الظرف)",
      "titleArabic": "المفعول فيه / الظرف",
      "content": [
        "The ẓarf (adverb) indicates the time or place of an action. It is a type of maf'ūl fīhi and is always in the accusative case."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Time adverbs: صَبَاحًا, مَسَاءً, يَوْمًا, لَيْلًا",
        "Place adverbs: أَمَامَ, خَلْفَ, فَوْقَ, تَحْتَ",
        "Some are indeclinable (mabnī): إِذْ, حَيْثُ, أَمْسِ",
        "Always manṣūb when declinable"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "جَلَسْتُ تَحْتَ الشَّجَرَةِ", "english": "I sat under the tree" },
        { "arabic": "سَافَرَ صَبَاحًا", "english": "He traveled in the morning" }
      ]
    }
